      <hedline>
        <hl1>Behavior at a Debate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Patricia Rosenblad letter criticizes Rick Lazio's behavior during recent debate with Hillary Clinton in New York Senate campaign</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lazio Says Debate Critics Are Sexist'' (news article, Sept. 20):</p>
        <p>Representative Rick A. Lazio is trying to use sexism as an excuse for inappropriate behavior. But barging into a debate opponent's space is boorish and exceeds proper limits of debate, no matter what the sex of the opponent.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lazio Says Debate Critics Are Sexist'' (news article, Sept. 20):</p>
        <p>Representative Rick A. Lazio is trying to use sexism as an excuse for inappropriate behavior. But barging into a debate opponent's space is boorish and exceeds proper limits of debate, no matter what the sex of the opponent.</p>
        <p>In addition, Mr. Lazio's personal attack on Hillary Rodham Clinton concerning the actions of her mate is unfeeling and unethical. It's O.K. to go after her on political matters, but to bash her because her husband caused her pain is reprehensible.</p>
        <p>PATRICIA ROSENBLAD  North Brunswick, N.J., Sept. 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
